name: Artisan at Asante
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Proposed amenity
amenities.description: Proposed amenity complex including a recreation center, multi-purpose room, fitness studio, movement studio, community pool, shaded lap pool, tot lot, 8 pickleball courts, half basketball court, activity lawn, outdoor fireplace with seating, outdoor games, and more!

amenities.name: existing Asante
amenities.description: The existing Asante masterplan community includes a large city park with lighted baseball and soccer fields and a public library

amenities.name: Easy access
amenities.description: Easy access to Loop 303 and State Route 60

amenities.name: Close proximity
amenities.description: Close proximity to major job corridors including the new Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC) site
